&lt;p&gt;As a Principal Cloud Alliance PartnerManager, you will lead and expand our global strategic partnership with AWS. In this role, you will be responsible for driving joint go-to-market initiatives, deepening technical integrations, executing agreements, and maximizing revenue opportunities through AWS programs and sales motions. This position requires a highly strategic and execution-focused leader with a deep understanding of the AWS ecosystem, cloud technologies, and partner management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own &amp;amp; Scale the AWS Partnership: Lead Datadog’s global alliance strategy with AWS, managing key executive and field relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Revenue Growth: Identify and execute joint business opportunities, including marketplace transactions, co-selling initiatives, and AWS funding programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go-to-Market Leadership: Collaborate with AWS and internal teams (sales, marketing, and product) to develop and launch integrated solutions, campaigns, and enablement programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical &amp;amp; Product Alignment: Work closely with Datadog’s product and engineering teams to strengthen AWS integrations and ensure technical alignment with AWS services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field &amp;amp; Partner Enablement: Train and support Datadog’s global sales teams on AWS partnership benefits, co-sell motions, and marketplace offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure &amp;amp; Optimize: Track partnership performance using key metrics (pipeline, revenue, AWS incentives) and continuously refine strategy to maximize impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in 10+ years of partner-facing business development, strategic alliances, or channel sales at a cloud services or software as a service organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in driving sales, partner sourced and partner influenced opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to quickly understand technical concepts and explain them to others verbally and in writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Cloud Alliances and Tech Alliances (other ISVs) a plus.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That&#39;s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and Growth:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High income earning opportunities based on self performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New hire stock equity (RSU) and employee stock purchase plan (ESPP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous professional development, product training, and career pathing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sales training in MEDDIC and Command of the Message&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intra-departmental mentor and buddy program for in-house networking&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An inclusive company culture, opportunity to join our Community Guilds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous global benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits and Growth listed above may vary based on the country of your employment and the nature of your employment with Datadog.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Datadog offers a competitive salary and equity package, and may include variable compensation. Actual compensation is based on factors such as the candidate&#39;s skills, qualifications, and experience. In addition, Datadog offers a wide range of best in class, comprehensive and inclusive employee benefits for this role including healthcare, dental, parental planning, and mental health benefits, a 401(k) plan and match, paid time off, fitness reimbursements, and a discounted employee stock purchase plan.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;The reasonably estimated yearly salary for this role at Datadog is:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$170,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$240,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Datadog:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog (NASDAQ: DDOG) is a global SaaS business, delivering a rare combination of growth and profitability. We are on a mission to break down silos and solve complexity in the cloud age by enabling digital transformation, cloud migration, and infrastructure monitoring of our customers’ entire technology stacks. Built by engineers, for engineers, Datadog is used by organizations of all sizes across a wide range of industries. Together, we champion professional development, diversity of thought, innovation, and work excellence to empower continuous growth. Join the pack and become part of a collaborative, pragmatic, and thoughtful people-first community where we solve tough problems, take smart risks, and celebrate one another. Learn more about #DatadogLife on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.instagram.com/datadoghq/?hl=en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/datadog&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;LinkedIn,&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://learn.datadoghq.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Datadog Learning Center. &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;215&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Equal Opportunity at Datadog:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog is proud to offer &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.eeoc.gov/sites/default/files/2023-06/22-088_EEOC_KnowYourRights6.12ScreenRdr.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;equal employment opportunity&lt;/a&gt; to everyone regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, veteran status, and other characteristics protected by law. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. Here are our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/candidate-legal-notices/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Candidate Legal Notices&lt;/a&gt; for your reference.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog endeavors to make our Careers Page accessible to all users. If you would like to contact us regarding the accessibility of our website or need assistance completing the application process, please complete &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeoJeduEZ2NdZF_65uZmWUrCM-zee7yADXX1s6Xr9zAGq8iKA/viewform&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;this form&lt;/a&gt;. This form is for accommodation requests only and cannot be used to inquire about the status of applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;662&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Privacy and AI Guidelines:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;662&quot;&gt;Any information you submit to Datadog as part of your application will be processed in accordance with Datadog’s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/applicant-candidate-privacy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/applicant-candidate-privacy/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Applicant and Candidate Privacy Notice&lt;/a&gt;. For information on our AI policy, please visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/interviewing-at-datadog-ai-guidelines/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Interviewing at Datadog AI Guidelines&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Customers depend on Datadog’s Incident Management product in crisis moments — when outages threaten their business — and your work will shape how teams respond and learn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager II, you’ll own the product that turns chaos into calm: declaring incidents, rallying responders, coordinating remediation, and turning every outage into a learning opportunity that prevents the next one. This is a broad, technically rich product — you’ll own features across real-time UIs, automation, AI-powered summaries and recommendations, documentation and runbooks, task and incident state management, analytics, and deep integrations with third-party chat and video platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll own the features that reduce Mean Time to Resolution (MTTR) for some of the world’s most complex cloud systems, partnering closely with the rest of the product organization to deliver end-to-end incident response. Your work will be highly visible to customers and internal stakeholders and will shape how organizations run reliable services at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog is uniquely positioned to deliver best-in-class end-to-end incident response by surfacing the right telemetry (metrics, traces, logs), orchestrating responders through alerting and paging, and closing the loop with automation and incident management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of the incident process of our our dev, ops, and security customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end product management process for the Incident Management product within Datadog&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ship features to help our customers respond to outages faster&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be accountable for the growth of the Datadog incident management product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Design and Engineering teams to develop product priorities and roadmaps that inspire our teams’ best work and deliver real value&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the Sales, Account Management, Marketing and Solutions teams to close deals and support existing customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) for the product and report on them to business and executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An experienced Product Manager, ideally at a SaaS company&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are customer-minded with a high quality standard for the product to be delivered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent verbal and written communication skills and the willingness to present and defend your ideas to both technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a strong sense of the day in the life of an engineer who holds a pager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or Engineering or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We know not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That’s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your experience, we encourage you to apply.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Growth:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New hire stock equity (RSUs) and employee stock purchase plan (ESPP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous professional development, product training, and career pathing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intra-departmental mentor and buddy program for in-house networking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An inclusive company culture, ability to join our Community Guilds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to Inclusion Talks, our Internal panel discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free, global Spring Health benefits for employees and dependents age 6+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive global benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits and Growth listed above may vary based on the country of your employment and the nature of your employment with Datadog.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Datadog offers a competitive salary and equity package, and may include variable compensation. Actual compensation is based on factors such as the candidate&#39;s skills, qualifications, and experience. In addition, Datadog offers a wide range of best in class, comprehensive and inclusive employee benefits for this role including healthcare, dental, parental planning, and mental health benefits, a 401(k) plan and match, paid time off, fitness reimbursements, and a discounted employee stock purchase plan.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;The reasonably estimated yearly salary for this role at Datadog is:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$187,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$240,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Datadog:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog (NASDAQ: DDOG) is a global SaaS business, delivering a rare combination of growth and profitability. We are on a mission to break down silos and solve complexity in the cloud age by enabling digital transformation, cloud migration, and infrastructure monitoring of our customers’ entire technology stacks. Built by engineers, for engineers, Datadog is used by organizations of all sizes across a wide range of industries. Together, we champion professional development, diversity of thought, innovation, and work excellence to empower continuous growth. Join the pack and become part of a collaborative, pragmatic, and thoughtful people-first community where we solve tough problems, take smart risks, and celebrate one another. Learn more about #DatadogLife on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.instagram.com/datadoghq/?hl=en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Instagram&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/datadog&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;LinkedIn,&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://learn.datadoghq.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Datadog Learning Center. &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;215&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Equal Opportunity at Datadog:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog is proud to offer &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.eeoc.gov/sites/default/files/2023-06/22-088_EEOC_KnowYourRights6.12ScreenRdr.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;equal employment opportunity&lt;/a&gt; to everyone regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, veteran status, and other characteristics protected by law. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. Here are our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/candidate-legal-notices/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Candidate Legal Notices&lt;/a&gt; for your reference.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog endeavors to make our Careers Page accessible to all users. If you would like to contact us regarding the accessibility of our website or need assistance completing the application process, please complete &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeoJeduEZ2NdZF_65uZmWUrCM-zee7yADXX1s6Xr9zAGq8iKA/viewform&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;this form&lt;/a&gt;. This form is for accommodation requests only and cannot be used to inquire about the status of applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;662&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Privacy and AI Guidelines:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;662&quot;&gt;Any information you submit to Datadog as part of your application will be processed in accordance with Datadog’s&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/applicant-candidate-privacy/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/applicant-candidate-privacy/&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;Applicant and Candidate Privacy Notice&lt;/a&gt;. For information on our AI policy, please visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.datadoghq.com/legal/interviewing-at-datadog-ai-guidelines/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Interviewing at Datadog AI Guidelines&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At Datadog, we&#39;re on a relentless mission to build the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;best platform in the world &lt;/strong&gt;for engineers to truly understand and scale their systems, applications, and teams. Operating at an &lt;strong&gt;unprecedented scale&lt;/strong&gt; - processing trillions of data points per day - we empower seamless collaboration and problem-solving for tens of thousands of companies globally. Our engineering culture thrives on pragmatism, honesty, and simplicity, tackling complex challenges the right way.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SDLC Observability &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Datadog&#39;s Software Delivery Platform starts with a comprehensive, end-to-end visibility across the entire SDLC, helping customers catch issues before production, optimize costs, and accelerate delivery. Our product suite includes granular insights into CI/CD pipelines, intelligent test management and optimization, code quality gates, and automated DORA metrics across every major CI provider. This is more than monitoring; it&#39;s about preventing failures, removing bottlenecks and eliminating developer disruptions at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Runtime, Machine learning and Curiosity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a continued curiosity to explore uncharted spaces while innovating in more established ones. With the rise of AI-generated code, the volume of Pull Requests, CI runs, and Tests is growing fast, creating more noise, higher costs, and new bottlenecks for engineering teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re tackling the impact of that growth on SDLC by absorbing and root-cause fixing CI instability, and generating/updating/orchestrating thousands of tests using production signals and quantifying how AI impacts SDLC. We have an appetite to solve hard problems in clever ways. Our users trust us with their observability data and we work hard to put it to good use for them.&amp;nbsp;At Datadog, we are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Product Manager II&lt;/strong&gt; to help us evolve the &lt;strong&gt;Software Delivery Suit to work on all these spaces&lt;/strong&gt; to help developers ship faster, safer, and with less cognitive&amp;nbsp;load.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds, and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uncover Developer / Platform Eng Needs: &lt;/strong&gt;You will conduct user research and analyze&amp;nbsp;usage data to understand how teams at different scales (from startups to massive&amp;nbsp;enterprises) struggle with pipeline noise, testing and deployment risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Owning and accelerating parts of the Software Delivery business: &lt;/strong&gt;Drive adoption of&amp;nbsp;CI/CD Visibility, Test Optimization, and Code Quality products, optimize customer&amp;nbsp;onboarding, and ensure robust revenue growth across Platform Engineers and&amp;nbsp;Developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define the experience: &lt;/strong&gt;From intuitive pipeline visibility to intelligent test selection,&amp;nbsp;quality gates, and Auto Test generation - ensuring every developer ships code with&amp;nbsp;confidence and speed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategize to win the market:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with Product Marketing and Sales to perfect&amp;nbsp;positioning while enabling field teams to articulate how we help in the larger Datadog&amp;nbsp;suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Thinker:&lt;/strong&gt; You have &lt;strong&gt;3-5 years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; in Product Management or a&amp;nbsp;combined background in Engineering/DevOps and Product. You understand how to&amp;nbsp;break down big problems into shippable iterations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developer Empathy: &lt;/strong&gt;You have a technical background or a strong familiarity with the&amp;nbsp;SDLC. You understand concepts like &lt;strong&gt;CI pipelines (GitHub Actions, GitLab), Test&amp;nbsp;Flakiness, Deployment strategies (Canary, Blue/Green)&lt;/strong&gt;, and why developers hate&amp;nbsp;being blocked by infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-Driven: &lt;/strong&gt;You are comfortable with analytics tools to query usage data, prove a&amp;nbsp;hypothesis, and measure the success of a feature launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adaptable:&lt;/strong&gt; You are comfortable with ambiguity. Our strategy involves moving fast to&amp;nbsp;solve new problems created by AI coding assistants; you are excited to pivot focus&amp;nbsp;between Testing, CI, and Deployments based on where the biggest value lies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborator: &lt;/strong&gt;You have excellent communication skills and can work effectively with&amp;nbsp;distributed engineering teams, building consensus and keeping projects on track.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That&#39;s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
