&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure, troubleshoot, monitor, and administer our catalog of SaaS applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain integrations between our SaaS applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate workflows and tasks to increase efficiency across our SaaS application catalog.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our Engineering and Business Systems teams to improve SaaS experiences for our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a point of escalation for the IT Support team on SaaS-related issues and participate in an on-call rotation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain documentation related to SaaS application policies, procedures, and features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience in administering Google Workspace and other common SaaS applications such as Slack and Zoom.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience with automation and APIs across a variety of SaaS platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are familiar with regulated environments including SOC II, SOX and FedRAMP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are familiar with Single Sign-On technologies such as SAML.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a passion for learning new tools and technologies while working in a fast-paced, high growth startup environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
